MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: \.claude/(settings(\.local)?\.json|hooks/.+\.(sh|js|ts))$
ADVISORY: |
  Hooks run SHELL COMMANDS, not model turns. They cannot:
    - Invoke slash commands (/reflect, /exit, etc.)
    - Make the model take another turn of reasoning/tool-use
    - Run agents except via `type: agent`/`type: prompt` hooks — and those
      are restricted to PreToolUse | PostToolUse | PermissionRequest only.

  So `SessionEnd` / `Stop` cannot "auto-run /reflect", "auto-run /commit",
  or anything that needs LLM reasoning. The best they can do is print a
  `systemMessage` or write a file that the next session surfaces.

  If a user asks "can we fire X automatically when the session ends?":
    - Shell task (git status check, log rotation, cache clear) → SessionEnd ✓
    - LLM task (review session, draft a handoff, decide to commit) → NO. Use a
      UserPromptSubmit nudge to remind the user to invoke the slash command
      while they're still in a live turn.

  `additionalContext` injection is only available on UserPromptSubmit,
  PreToolUse, SessionStart — not Stop/SessionEnd. Don't try to bolt it on.
